Daniel Boykin, 33, was sentenced to six months prison for unlawful photography, aggravated burglary, wiretapping and two computer crimes on Thursday . 
  Boykin was fired from the Transportation Security Administration after he was found with 92 videos and 1,500 photos of his victim in his phone and computer . 
  He repeatedly filmed the woman at Nashville International Airport and broke into her home five times . 
  He admitted to stalking the woman in court Thursday and pleaded guilty to unlawful photography . 
 